- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses a novel 4x4 reversible gate and its application in constructing reversible comparators, which can be considered an emerging technology in the field of low power VLSI circuit design. 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper presents a new design style for reversible circuits and discusses the structure of binary group-based n-bit comparators, which can be considered an architectural aspect of circuit design. 
- cs.DC (Digital Circuits): The paper deals with the design and implementation of digital circuits using reversible logic, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper discusses the power and delay characteristics of the proposed circuits, which can be related to the electromagnetic properties of the circuits. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper deals with the design and implementation of logic circuits using reversible gates, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
